			<div id="header"><a id="Rules">Rules</a></div>
			<br>
			<div id="contenido">
				<p>
					<h2>INGENIOUS PROFICIENCY</h2>
					When creating a character, you gain a number of points equal to your <b>Intelligence modifier</b> (minimum of 0).
					<br>
					<br>
					When you permanently increase your <b>Intelligence modifier,</b> you may spend additional points as normal. Proficiencies learned by spending points <b>cannot be lost once gained.</b>
					<br>
					<br>
					<table class="tablacentral">
						<tr><th class="td1">Benefit</th><th class="td1">Cost</th></tr>
						<tr><td class="td2">Additional Class or Background Skill proficiency</td><td class="td1">2</td></tr>
						<tr><td class="td2">Double proficiency for a Skill you are proficient in</td><td class="td1">3</td></tr>
						<tr><td class="td2">Learn an additional language</td><td class="td1">1</td></tr>
						<tr><td class="td2">Tool proficiency</td><td class="td1">1</td></tr>
						<tr><td class="td2">Double proficiency for a Tool you are proficient with</td><td class="td1">2</td></tr>
						<tr><td class="td2">Proficiency with 3 Simple or 2 Martial weapons</td><td class="td1">1</td></tr>
					</table>
					<br>
					<br>
					<h2>IMPROVED INSPIRATION</h2>
					<b>Both the players and the DM</b> start each session with 1 inspiration point. This inspiration can be used <b>to reroll any die roll</b> made by anyone, but another player can choose to refuse the inspiration in which case the inspiration is not lost.
					<br>
					<br>
					<br>
					<h2>IMPROVED HEALING POTION</h2>
					When you drink a healing potion, don't roll a d4 ,instead <b>roll the same die as your largest hit die and spend these hit dies</b>. If you don't have a hit die value for any reason, roll a d4. 
					<br>
					<br>
					<b><u>Potion of Healing :</u> 2d(hitdice) + 2 ; <u>Potion of Greater Healing :</u> 4d(hitdice) + 4 ; etc...</b>
					<br>
					<br>
					<br>
					<h2>ADDITIONAL ATTACKS</h2>
					When you get a feature that <b>adds a single attack</b> as a <b>bonus action</b> instead <b>you add it to your attack action</b>. For example Two weapon fighting would now count as an extra attack. This effect can happen <b>once per turn</b>, after this first time you will need to use your bonus action normally.
					<br>
					<br>
					<br>
					<h2>OPPORTUNITY ATTACKS</h2>
				   Instead of provoking opportunity attacks when leaving range, creatures provoke them <b>when they move within your range</b>. This doesnt apply when entering someones range.
				<br>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div id="footer">Página 1</div>
			
		</div>
		<div class="hojavertical">
		
		 
			<div id="contenido3">
				<p>
				<br>
				<br>
				<h2>SURGICAL HEALING <mark>(optional)</mark></h2>
				Including additional healing kits so parties without a healer can do better.
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Healer's kit</b> - As an action, you can expend one use of the kit to stabilize a creature that has 0 hit points, without needing to make a Wisdom (Medicine) check. <b>Cost (5gp) Weight: 3 lbs</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Medical Kit</b> - Heals an additional 1d10 hp. <b>Cost (50gp) Weight: 5 lbs</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Surgeon kit</b> - It heals an additional 15 hp. Additionally you can do a medicine check (DC20) to a creature that has died in the last minute to bring him back to life. This action consumes 5 charges. <b>Cost (250gp) Weight: 8 lbs</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				<h2>FALL UNCONSCIOUS</h2>
				When you <b>fall unconscius you gain 1 point of exhaustion.</b> Additionally you <b>can use 1 hit die to recover 1 point of exhaustion.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				<h2>REVISED FLANKING</h2>
				You may flank any creature but <b>you only gain advantage on the first attack</b> on each of your turns.				
				<br>
				<br>
				
				<h2>TAKE AIM</h2>
				If a creature <b>didnt move last turn</b> it can choose to <b>gain advantage on the first ranged attack</b> it makes this turn and reduce its speed to 0 for the rest of it.				
				<br>
				<br>
				<h2>MAGIC ITEM PRICES</h2>
				This is the website that the master uses to revamp prices on magic items: 
				 <a href="https://forums.giantitp.com/showthread.php?424243-Sane-Magic-Item-Prices">HERE</a>
				<br>
				<br>
				</p>
			</div>
					
			<div id="footer">Página 2</div>
			
			</div>
		
		
		<div class="hojavertical">
		
			<div id="header"><a id="Changed_Feats">Multiple Changes</a></div>

			<div id="contenido2">
				<h1 style="background-color: #AE3133">NEW FEATS</h1>
				<p>
				<h2>LIGHT WEAPON MASTER</h2>
				- While holding a light melee weapon that you are proficient with in each hand, before you make and attack with one of the weapons, <b>you can choose to take a -5 penalty to the attack roll.</b> If the attack hits, <b>you add the base weapon damage dice<b> of the off-hand weapon</b> together with the damage of the main attack for the attack's damage and <b>your ability modifier is doubled (if it applies)</b>, as you strike with both weapons simultaneously.
				<br>
				<br>
				- Whenever you make an attack, <b>you can draw a light melee weapons as part of taking the attack.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- On your turn, when <b>you score a critical hit with a melee weapon</b> or <b>reduce a creature to 0 hit points</b> with one, your <b>movement speed</b> is increased by <b>15 feet</b> until the end of your turn.
				<br>
				<h2>FRONTLINE CHARGER</h2>
				Your fighting prowess allows you to become the vanguard of any army. You gain the following benefits: 
				<br>
				<br>
				- Increase your <b>Strength, Dexterity or Constitution by 1</b>, to a maximum of 20.
				<br>
				<br>
				- You can use <b>your Dash as a bonus action</b> when you move toward a hostile creature.  If you have moved at least 20 ft. with this dash, you can <b>add your ability modifier twice to the next damage roll</b> you make with a melee weapon and you can also <b>shove the first creature</b> you hit with <b>advantage.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- If flanked by any creature, you can use <b>your reaction to negate any flanking bonuses against you</b> until the end of your next turn. This ability can be used a number of times equal to <b>your proficiency modifier</b> and recharges after a long rest.
				<br>
				<h2>COMBAT BLADE MASTER</h2>
				- Every combat blade <b>gains the parry property</b> for you. If that combat blade already had parry, <b>the amount of AC</b> it gives to the triggering attack <b>increases by 1.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- If you <b>successfully parry</b> an attack using a combat blade <b>your AC increases by 1 until the start of your next turn</b>. If your weapon has the <b>riposte property</b>, you may use riposte <b>if an attack misses because of this additional AC</b> and you are in the following stance.
				<br>
				<br>
				- While holding a combat blade you may <b>use your bonus action to enter a readied stance</b>. While in this stance you gain <b>an additional reaction</b> that you may <b>only use for melee attacks</b> with combat blades.
				<br>
				<br>			
				♦ The following weapons count as Combat Blades for this feat: <span style="color:#960F77">Dao, Broadsword, Falchion, Katana, Longsword,O-Katana, Rapier, Scimitar, Shortsword, Swordbreaker Dagger.</span>
				<br>					
				</p>
			</div>
			<br>
			<br>
			<div id="footer">Página 3</div>
			
		</div>
		
		<div class="hojavertical">
			<div id="header"></div>
		
			<div id="contenido2">
				<p>
				<h2>HEAVY BLADE MASTER</h2>
				- Increase your <b>Strength or Constitution by 1</b>, to a maximum of 20.
				<br>
				<br>
				- You may shove a creature using a heavy blade. <b>This shove</b> if successful deals <b>half the damage die of the weapon (rounded up) plus your STR mod.</b> You count as one size category larger for this shove.
				<br>
				<br>
				- On your turn, when <b>you score a critical hit</b> with a heavy blade or <b>reduce a creature to 0 hit points</b> with one, you may apply the <b>brutal trait without needing a crit on the next attack</b> you make before the start of your next turn. 
				<br>
				<br>
				♦ The following weapons count as Heavy Blades for this feat: <span style="color:#960F77">Bastard Sword, Full Blade, GreatSword, O-Katana, Zweihänder.</span>
				<br>			
				<h2>AXE MASTER</h2>
				- Increase your <b>Strength or Constitution by 1</b>, to a maximum of 20.
				<br>
				<br>
				- When you <b>roll a 1 or 2 on a damage die</b> for an attack you make with an axe, you can <b>reroll the die</b> and must use the new roll, even if the new roll is a 1 or a 2.
				<br>
				<br>
				- When <b>you score a critical hit</b> while using an axe, the target has its <b>AC reduced by 1</b> for the next minute.
				<br>
				<br>
				♦ The following weapons count as Axes for this feat: <span style="color:#960F77">Handaxe, Bastard Axe (Bastard Sword variant), Battleaxe, Full Axe (Full blade variant), Greataxe.</span>
				<br>				
				<h2>BLUDGEON MASTER</h2>	
				- <b>+1 to attacks and damage</b> against enemies wearing <b>medium armor, heavy armor or any shield</b> that's not a buckler.
				<br>
				<br>
				- Whenever you <b>have disadvantage on attacks</b> and at least <b>one roll would have hit</b> but the other misses, you can deal your <b>strength modifier in weapon damage</b> to the target. This still counts as a miss.
				<br>
				<br>
				- <b>Once per turn,</b> when you hit a creature with a bludgeon, <b>you may try to shove a creature 5ft</b> away from you <b>as part of the attack.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				♦ The following weapons count as Bludgeons for this feat: <span style="color:#960F77">Light Hammer, Mace, Bastard Hammer (Bastard Sword variant), Full Maul (Full Blade variant), Maul, Morningstar, Warhammer.</span>
				<br>
				<h2>SPEAR MASTER</h2>				
				- Increase your <b>Strength, Dexterity or Constitution by 1</b>, to a maximum of 20.
				<br>
				<br>
				- <b>You ignore the penalty of the charge property.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- When you <b>first attack a creature entering your range</b> (be because of polearm master or because you prepared your action), this attack is made with <b>advantage and applies the damage boost of charge.</b>
				<br>
				<br>					
				♦ The following weapons count as Spears for this feat: <span style="color:#960F77">Javelin, Spear,Lance, Long Spear, Pike, Trident.</span>
				<br>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div id="footer">Página 4</div>
		</div>
		
		<div class="hojavertical">
			<div id="header"></div>
			<div id="contenido2">
				<p>
				<h2>FLAIL AND WHIP MASTER</h2>
				- Increase your <b>Strength or Dexterity DC by 1.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- When you hit a <b>large or smaller creature with an opportunity attack,</b> that creature must make a <b>Strength saving throw against your Strength or Dexterity DC</b> (depending on your weapon) or <b>fall Prone.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- On the <b>first attack you make each turn,</b> you may apply the <b>shield-wrap bonus</b> to an attack made against a <b>creature without a shield.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				♦ The following weapons count as Flails and Whips for this feat: <span style="color:#960F77">Flail, Heavy Flail, Kusarigama, Whip, Whip-Dagger.</span>
				<br>
				<h2>BOW AND SLING MASTER</h2>
				- Increase your <b>Dexterity by 1</b>, to a maximum of 20.
				<br>
				<br>
				- <b>Once per turn</b> when you make a <b>ranged attack,</b> you may choose make an <b>additional attack to an additional creature within 5ft</b> of the first objective. If you choose to attack this way, the attack targeting the <b>second creature</b> is made with <b>disadvantage.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- <b>If you haven't moved this turn,</b> you may use <b>your reaction</b> to <b>reduce your speed to 0</b> and <b>gain advantage on the first attack</b> you make this turn.
				<br>
				<br>
				♦ The following weapons count as Bows and Slings for this feat: <span style="color:#960F77">Shortbow, Sling, Slingshot, Greatbow, Longbow.</span>
				<br>
				<h2>FIREARM TRAINEE</h2>
				- Your <b>Dexterity increases by 1.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- <b>You gain proficiency with firearms.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- Being within <b>5ft of a hostile creature does not impose disadvantage</b> on your ranged weapon attack rolls.
				<br>
				<h2>FIREARM MASTER</h2>
				- <b>You ignore the loading property.</b>
				<br>
				<br>
				- Weapons with the <b>spread property count as melee weapons</b> for the purposes of <b>disadvantage, flanking and opportunity attacks</b> when used within 5ft of a creature and weapons with the <b>caliber property roll 3d20 instead of 2d20</b> when having <b>advantage</b> on an attack roll.
				<br>
				<br>
				- If you roll a <b>misfire on an attack</b> with a firearm, you can use <b>your reaction to roll a d20.</b> If the number rolled is <b>higher than the weapon’s misfire score,</b> the firearm does not misfire. You cannot use this feature of this feat again until you complete a <b>short or long rest.</b>
				<br>
				</p>
			</div>
