		<div class="hojavertical">
				
				<div id="contenido">
				<p>
				<h2>SPECIAL WEAPONS</h2>
				<b>Bastard Sword.</b> This particular weapon is too large to wield in one hand normally unless you meet a specific strength requirement. You must have a Strength score of at least 19 or suffer disadvantage on all attacks made with this weapon. Additionally this weapon may apply the brutal trait even when used with one hand.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Boomerang.</b> This weapon will return to you if you fail to hit your target. Using your reaction, you can catch it by succeeding a DC 10 Dexterity check.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				
				<b>Broadsword.</b> This weapon may apply the brutal trait while being a one-handed weapon.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Cestus.</b> Donning or doffing this glove-like weapon requires an action and you may hold another weapon in the same hand as the cestus. Unarmed strikes deal 1d4 <img src="hammer.png"> damage whilst the cestus worn.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Double Scimitar.</b> You can treat this weapon as if you are dual wielding and apply any relevant feats when wielding this weapon
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Double-Bladed Sword.</b> You can treat this weapon as if you are dual wielding and apply any relevant feats when wielding this weapon but it needs either the Dual Wielder feat or the Revenant Blade feat to be used without disadvantage.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Full Blade.</b> This particular weapon is too large to wield normally unless you meet a specific strength requirement. You must have a Strength score of at least 19 or suffer disadvantage on all attacks made with this weapon.
				
				<br>
				
				<br>
				
				<br>
				
				<b>Greatbow.</b> You need at least a 17 Strength score to use effectively, or you have disadvantage on attack rolls with it. You use your Strength modifier for attack and damage rolls. You can use javelins as ammunition.
				
				<br>
				
				<br>
				
				<br>
				
				<b>Harpoon.</b> Whenever you land an attack with this weapon, it pierces into the enemy. They can choose to pull it out and deal an additional 1d10 of damage. As long as it remains in their body and you are holding on to the rope that the harpoon is attached to, they cannot move further away than 30 feet from you. They can attempt to yank the rope out of your hand by making a Strength check versus your own Strength check. Otherwise, they have to cut the line or pull out the harpoon to escape.
				
				<br>
				
				<br>
				
				<br>
				
				<b>Kusarigama.</b> This sickle-like weapon has a chain with a weight at the end. When you make a ranged attack by throwing the kusarigama you can pull the weapon back to your hand by the chain as part of the attack.
				
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				
				<b>Lance.</b> You have disadvantage when you use a lance to Attack a target within 5 feet of you. Also, a lance requires two hands to wield when you aren’t mounted.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>O-Katana.</b> This particular weapon is too large to wield in one hand normally unless you meet a specific strength requirement. You must have a Strength score of at least 19 or suffer disadvantage on all attacks made with this weapon.
				
				</p>
				</div>
				<div id="footer" style="margin-top: 70px">Página 11</div>
			
		</div>
		<div class="hojavertical">
			
				<div id="header"></div>
				<br>
				<div id="contenido">
				<p>
				<h2></h2>				
				<b>Rapier.</b> You may use this weapon to dual wield as long as it is with a dagger without requiring the dual wielder feat.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Slingshot.</b> This ranged weapon utilizes ball bearings as ammunition.
				
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				
				<b>Swordbreaker.</b> When you hit with this weapon a creature of your size or smaller thats wielding a slashing weapon, the creature must make a either STR or DEX Saving throw (its choice) or drop the weapon its currently carrying on its hands. if its a two-handed weapon it makes the Save with advantage.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Throwing knives.</b> You can throw up to 2 throwing knives as part of an attack when you take the attack action; for each thrown above the first you add an additional damage die.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>War Scythe.</b> If you have the polearm master feat you can wield this weapon with one hand if you have 19 STR.
				
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				
				<b>Whip.</b> When you hit with this weapon a creature of your size or smaller, the creature must make a either STR or DEX Saving throw (its choice) or drop the weapon or object its currently carrying on its hands. if its a two-handed object it makes the Save with advantage.
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Wrist Crossbow.</b> You cannot be disarmed of this weapon.
				
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
				
				<b>Zweihänder.</b> You require a Strength score of 15 or higher to use this weapon effectively, else your attacks have disadvantage.
				
				</p>
				</div>
				<div id="footer">Página 12</div>
			
		</div>
		
