				<table class="tabla_hojahorizontal" style="height: 200px">
					<tr class="tabla_hojahorizontal_datos"><th>Name</th><th style="width: 150px" >Cost</th><th colspan="4">Properties</th></tr>
					<tr class="tabla_hojahorizontal_definidor"><td colspan="6"><b><i>Ammo</i></b></td></tr>
					<tr class="tabla_hojahorizontal_filaimpar"><td>Normal Bullet</td><td>5gp per 20 bullets.</td><td colspan="4">--</td></tr>
					<tr class="tabla_hojahorizontal_filapar"><td>Tracing Bullet</td><td>15gp per 10 bullets</td><td colspan="4">Special</td></tr>
					<tr class="tabla_hojahorizontal_filaimpar"><td>Long Round</td><td>30gp per 10 bullets</td><td colspan="4">Special</td></tr>
					<tr class="tabla_hojahorizontal_filapar"><td>Explosive round</td><td>20gp per 5 rounds</td><td colspan="4">Special</td></tr>
					
					<tr class="tabla_hojahorizontal_definidor"><td colspan="6"><b><i>Tools</i></b></td></tr>
					
					<tr class="tabla_hojahorizontal_filapar"><td>Firearm Maintenance tools</td><td>150gp</td><td colspan="4">You may use this tools as part of a long rest to ignore the next missfire you suffer. This tools has 10 uses.</td></tr>
				</table>
				
				<h2>SPECIAL AMMO</h2>
				<b>Every type of ammo can be made magical for 3 times the original price.</b>
				
				<br>
				<br>
				
				<b>Tracing Bullet.</b> The target takes 1d6 fire damage at the start of each of its turns and cannot benefit from the effects of invisibility for 1 min. When the creature takes this damage it may make a Con save against your attack DC to end this effect prematurely.
				
				<br>
				<br>
				<b>Long Round.</b> When you hit a creature with this bullet you may make an additional attack against a creature within 5ft of the original one thats on a direct line from you, if this attack hits, that second creature takes damage equal to half the damage the original creature took.
				<br>
				
				<br>
				
				<b>Explosive Round.</b> Ignore the damage of the weapon and deal 1d8 fire damage to every creature within 5ft of the target including the target itself.
				<div id="contenido">
				<h2>SPECIAL PROPERTIES</h2>
					<b>Spread.</b> When you make an attack with this weapon within your "close" range, you may choose to forgo your normal attack to force all creatures in the area to make a Dexterity Saving Throw with a DC equal to your attack DC or receive the damage. This attack doesn't add your ability modifier to the damage. This type of attack counts as a melee attack for the purposes of flanking. Spread weapons cant use Explosive rounds.
					<br>
					<br>
					<b>Caliber.</b> When you score a critical hit with this weapon you deal an additional die of damage.
					<br>
					<br>
					<b>Misfire.</b> Whenever you make an attack roll with a firearm, and the dice roll is equal to or lower than the weapon’s Misfire score, the weapon misfires. The attack misses, and the weapon cannot be used again until you spend an action to try and repair it. To repair your firearm, you must make a successful Tinker’s Tools check (DC equal to 8 + misfire score). If your check fails, the weapon is broken and must be mended out of combat at a quarter of the cost of the firearm. Creatures who use a firearm without being proficient increase the weapon’s misfire score by 1.
					<br>
					<br>
					<b>Reload.</b> The weapon can be fired a number of times equal to its Reload score before you must spend 1 attack or 1 action to reload. You must have one free hand to reload a firearm.
				</div>
			</div>
			
